      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through individual throttle bodies and a high-revving 8,000 RPM redline. Mated to a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transmission, the drivetrain is anchored by a factory M Variable Differential Lock for optimal corner-exit traction. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including VANOS servicing and rear subframe reinforcement to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. The chassis remains taut with refreshed bushings and a responsive MacPherson strut front/multi-link rear suspension geometry. While showing minor signs of use consistent with its 'good' designation, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response remain razor-sharp. A true driver\u2019s specification for those who value analog feedback and engineering purity.",
